        <h2>Interpreting Your Science Marksheet from MGSU Bikaner</h2>
        <p>A science marksheet on the Univindia Net portal contains detailed information that is essential for understanding your academic standing. It is important to comprehend the breakdown for BSc students:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Theory vs. Practical Marks:</strong> BSc students must pass in both theory and practical components separately for most subjects. Ensure that both sets of marks are correctly reflected in the marksheet.</li>
            <li><strong>Aggregate Percentage:</strong> Your total marks obtained in the current year compared to the maximum marks possible. For BSc Final year students, the aggregate of all three years is also displayed.</li>
            <li><strong>Final Academic Status:</strong> This will indicate whether you have 'Passed', 'Failed', or have been awarded a 'Supplementary' (SUPP).</li>
            <li><strong>Common Science Abbreviations:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>PR:</strong> Practical Exam.</li>
                    <li><strong>TH:</strong> Theory Exam.</li>
                    <li><strong>RW:</strong> Result Withheld (usually due to missing practical marks or previous year discrepancies).</li>
                    <li><strong>INC:</strong> Incomplete (marks for one component are still pending with the university).</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

